subcellularLocation.summary: Localized to nucleus and nuclear membrane.

tissueExpression.summary: A majority of the normal tissues showed moderate to strong nuclear immunoreactivity which sometimes was combined with weaker cytoplasmic positivity. Non-neuronal cells of the CNS were generally negative.

A majority of the malignant cells displayed moderate to strong nuclear immunoreactivity which sometimes was combined with weaker cytoplasmic positivity. Malignant gliomas and basal cell carcinomas of the skin showed weak staining in a majority of cases.
